FT  01 NOV 94 / TVR to boost car production
TVR, the Blackpool-based independent sports car maker, is doubling the size
of its manufacturing plant and starting its first night shift to build a
third range of cars and expand production.
The company said last night that it had taken orders worth Pounds 10m for
the Cerbera, a new 2 + 2 coupe model exhibited at last week's UK motor show.
The British Motor Centenary Trust announced plans yesterday for the
celebration of 100 years of the motor industry in Britain with more than 60
special events planned to take place in 1996.
